title: Checkpoint Firewalls: High Availability Problems
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/network/checkpoint
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk

item:
 Name of the HA Module

description:
 This check monitors problems in the High Availability Module.
 The status is {CRIT} if a problem has been signaled, {OK} otherwise.
 The device reports a list of possible problems and a signaled state for
 each.
 In the devices observed so far the problem categories were called
 "Filter", "Synchronization", "cphad" and "fwd".

inventory:
 One service is created for each problem category.

